  "prompt": "How do you improve footwork?",
  "response": "To improve footwork, try these methods:\n\n1. Jump Rope\n- Enhances coordination\n- Develops rhythm and timing\n- Improves foot speed and agility\n\n2. Ladder Drills\n- Quick stepping through agility ladders\n- Various patterns like in-and-out, lateral steps\n- Develops precise foot placement\n\n3. Cone Drills\n- Set up cones in different configurations\n- Practice quick direction changes\n- Improve acceleration and deceleration\n\n4. Shadow Boxing/Shadowwork\n- Practice footwork while throwing punches\n- Focus on balance and movement\n- Great for sports like boxing, martial arts\n\n5. Plyometric Exercises\n- Box jumps\n- Skipping\n- Lateral bounds\n- Develops explosive power and quickness\n\n6. Sport-Specific Drills\n- Practice footwork specific to your sport\n- Basketball defensive slides\n- Soccer dribbling drills\n- Tennis court movement\n\n7. Dance and Coordination Exercises\n- Salsa, hip-hop, or dance classes\n- Improves overall body coordination\n- Enhances rhythm and movement\n\n8. Balance Training\n- Single-leg exercises\n- Stability ball work\n- Develops core strength and foot control\n\nConsistent practice and gradual progression are key to improving footwork.",
